You have to have patience.

254
00:34:56.994 --> 00:34:59.578
All good things will come to you.
You'll see.

255
00:35:08.296 --> 00:35:09.338
Excuse me.

256
00:35:09.423 --> 00:35:11.048
I'm sorry. we're closed.

257
00:35:11.091 --> 00:35:14.051
I would like to talk to you
about Thomas Aquinas.

258
00:35:14.594 --> 00:35:16.846
- Father. please. I need you downstairs.
- Just take these.

259
00:35:16.930 --> 00:35:18.848
- Father. please.
- Go.

260
00:35:21.768 --> 00:35:25.646
I've already told the police. Thomas
was a friend of mine and a colleague.

261
00:35:25.731 --> 00:35:28.274
He had nothing to do
with what happened today.

262
00:35:28.358 --> 00:35:30.484
Well. there was no one else
on that fire escape.

263
00:35:30.569 --> 00:35:31.777
You don't understand.

264
00:35:31.820 --> 00:35:34.613
I understand getting shot at.
and I don't like it.

265
00:35:34.698 --> 00:35:37.283
He shot at you?
No. he shot at my client.

266
00:35:37.325 --> 00:35:38.659
And I happened
to get in the way.

267
00:35:38.744 --> 00:35:39.910
Who's your client?

268
00:35:39.953 --> 00:35:41.620
That's irrelevant right now.

269
00:35:41.705 --> 00:35:44.457
What I want to know is why would
a priest try to kill someone?

270
00:35:44.541 --> 00:35:49.295
Listen. you've been drinking. I've got
14 years sober and I can spot that.

271
00:35:49.337 --> 00:35:50.463
Well. good for you.

272
00:35:50.547 --> 00:35:53.132
Your friend and colleague.
was he working for someone?

273
00:35:53.175 --> 00:35:55.176
Yes. he was working for God.

274
00:35:55.260 --> 00:35:57.928
So God ordered a hit
on an investment banker?

275
00:35:57.971 --> 00:35:59.805
There's an awful lot
that you don't know.

276
00:35:59.848 --> 00:36:01.223
You think you've
seen everything?

277
00:36:01.308 --> 00:36:03.601
You haven't. There are
things you never dreamed of.

278
00:36:03.643 --> 00:36:05.186
There's another world
out there!

279
00:36:05.270 --> 00:36:07.521
Thomas saw it
and it destroyed him.

280
00:36:07.814 --> 00:36:11.567
Well. I've seen a lot. too. but there's
nothing that would make me cut my tongue out.

281
00:36:11.651 --> 00:36:13.277
Yeah. well. wait a few days.

282
00:36:13.320 --> 00:36:15.154
What happens in a few days?

283
00:36:15.614 --> 00:36:18.032
Did Thomas tell you
about a girl?

284
00:36:20.410 --> 00:36:21.452
No.

285
00:36:22.120 --> 00:36:23.829
I see. Do you believe in God?

286
00:36:26.166 --> 00:36:29.376
Maybe once. But not anymore.

287
00:36:29.461 --> 00:36:31.003
What happened?

288
00:36:31.671 --> 00:36:33.631
We had a difference of opinion.

289
00:36:34.257 --> 00:36:36.967
I thought that my wife
and daughter should live.

290
00:36:37.427 --> 00:36:39.011
and he felt otherwise.

291
00:36:39.679 --> 00:36:40.971
I'm sorry to hear
about the loss.

292
00:36:41.014 --> 00:36:43.390
Maybe it's time for you
to renew your faith.

293
00:36:44.559 --> 00:36:45.851
This girl.

294
00:36:47.187 --> 00:36:49.563
Is she in trouble?
Does she need help?

295
00:36:49.648 --> 00:36:52.024
I have a lot of things to do here.
Excuse me.

296
00:36:52.067 --> 00:36:54.360
Excuse me. I have a few more
questions. if you don't mind.

297
00:36:54.402 --> 00:36:56.695
I've got a question for you.
If you don't believe in God.

298
00:36:56.738 --> 00:36:58.697
how can you understand
his adversary?

299
00:36:58.740 --> 00:37:01.992
Now I have to believe in God
in order to solve a crime?

300
00:37:02.994 --> 00:37:05.538
I'm sure that you can
find your way out.

301
00:37:43.702 --> 00:37:45.536
How many have received
the stigmata?

302
00:37:45.579 --> 00:37:47.246
She's the third this week.

303
00:37:51.751 --> 00:37:52.960
What is she saying?

304
00:37:53.044 --> 00:37:55.880
Please. for your own good. get
out and forget what you've seen.

305
00:37:55.922 --> 00:37:58.090
Was Thomas part of all this?
There are forces here at work

306
00:37:58.133 --> 00:38:01.844
you couldn't possibly comprehend!
Now. please. leave!

307
00:39:07.285 --> 00:39:11.121
No. it's just I hate the fact that
they put finals after the holiday.

308
00:39:11.164 --> 00:39:12.998
It ruins the whole meaning
of vacation.

309
00:39:13.041 --> 00:39:15.668
I wouldn't worry.
You always do fine.

310
00:39:15.710 --> 00:39:17.795
Besides. a bad grade
isn't the end of the world.

311
00:39:33.144 --> 00:39:34.395
It's you.

312
00:39:34.938 --> 00:39:37.022
- I didn't...
- Where is she?

313
00:39:37.274 --> 00:39:40.651
The girl is safe.
And what of the world?

314
00:39:41.194 --> 00:39:43.445
Everything is as planned.

315
00:39:43.530 --> 00:39:46.031
Our acts go unnoticed.
unquestioned.

316
00:39:46.074 --> 00:39:48.534
We're everywhere.
Daddy. who is it?

317
00:39:57.961 --> 00:40:00.629
- Is this your daughter?
- Yes.

318
00:40:04.342 --> 00:40:06.719
- This is your wife?
- Yes.

319
00:41:18.958 --> 00:41:21.794
- What's wrong. baby? What's wrong?
- It was a dream.

320
00:41:22.087 --> 00:41:25.130
He came for me again.
It's only a dream. angel.

321
00:41:25.465 --> 00:41:26.965
It felt closer.

322
00:41:32.972 --> 00:41:34.848
Throughout the country.
the National Guard

323
00:41:34.933 --> 00:41:37.184
has been put on alert
as a precaution in case...

324
00:41:37.268 --> 00:41:39.645
Rudolph Giuliani urged
all citizens and police

325
00:41:39.729 --> 00:41:41.313
to stay calm during
this holiday season.

326
00:41:41.398 --> 00:41:42.439
No explanations yet

327
00:41:42.482 --> 00:41:44.108
for how blood on the hands
of the Christ child.

328
00:41:44.150 --> 00:41:47.569
depicted in Michelangelo's famous
sculpture of the pieta...

329
00:41:47.654 --> 00:41:49.822
atmosphere of fear and
panic. random acts of violence

330
00:41:49.864 --> 00:41:52.741
are being attributed to satanic
cults who seem determined

331
00:41:52.826 --> 00:41:55.160
to disrupt New Year's celebrations
throughout the world.

332
00:41:55.245 --> 00:41:56.286
Here in New York...

333
00:42:13.179 --> 00:42:15.013
Sorry. pal.
you can't come in here.

334
00:42:17.475 --> 00:42:21.186
The young boys that you seduced
have left their scent upon you.

335
00:42:23.440 --> 00:42:26.024
Remember who it is
that you serve.

336
00:42:46.129 --> 00:42:48.005
Open your eyes. Thomas.

337
00:42:58.558 --> 00:43:01.477
Look. Look at the face
that has haunted your dreams

338
00:43:01.561 --> 00:43:03.020
for a thousand years.

339
00:43:20.538 --> 00:43:23.123
They say you can see
the future. Thomas.

340
00:43:25.293 --> 00:43:28.795
Then you must know exactly
what I'm going to do to you.

341
00:43:31.382 --> 00:43:33.467
We still don't know what we
hope to get from this guy.

342
00:43:33.551 --> 00:43:35.219
He's got no fucking tongue
for Christ's sake.

343
00:43:35.261 --> 00:43:36.345
He can write.

344
00:43:36.429 --> 00:43:40.057
Dr. Hansel. to surgery.
please. Dr. Hansel.

345
00:44:05.917 --> 00:44:07.125
Fuck me.

346
00:44:09.587 --> 00:44:11.630
There is still no explanation

347
00:44:11.673 --> 00:44:15.425
for the devastating explosions that
rocked Midtown two nights ago.

348
00:44:15.552 --> 00:44:17.594
In the wake of
Tuesday night's explosion.

349
00:44:17.637 --> 00:44:20.222
investigators from the
New York City Fire Department

350
00:44:20.306 --> 00:44:22.266
are still at a loss to explain

351
00:44:22.308 --> 00:44:26.061
why the restaurant suddenly burst
into flames. killing at least...

352
00:44:26.145 --> 00:44:28.021
Hey. asshole.
watch where you're going.

353
00:44:28.106 --> 00:44:29.856
Hey. I like the shirt.

354
00:44:31.025 --> 00:44:32.484
Screw you. man.

355
00:44:37.490 --> 00:44:38.699
Hey. kid.

356
00:44:44.664 --> 00:44:45.998
Nice shirt.

357
00:45:37.300 --> 00:45:40.010
I'm telling you. no one entered the room.
Maybe he did it himself.

358
00:45:40.053 --> 00:45:42.054
Then how did he get
the last scalpel in?

359
00:45:42.805 --> 00:45:44.097
Oh. my God.

360
00:45:44.182 --> 00:45:45.724
It just keeps getting better.

361
00:45:45.808 --> 00:45:48.268
I've never seen
anything like this.

362
00:45:52.065 --> 00:45:55.150
I think this is written
in Latin.

363
00:45:55.902 --> 00:45:59.404
"When the thousand
years has ended."

364
00:45:59.489 --> 00:46:04.451
"Satan shall be loosed
out of his prison."

365
00:46:06.537 --> 00:46:09.665
This next part is not clear.
I think it's in English.

366
00:46:09.749 --> 00:46:11.792
It says. "Christ..."

367
00:46:11.918 --> 00:46:14.961
"Christ in New York."

368
00:46:20.718 --> 00:46:21.968
Christ!

369
00:46:27.684 --> 00:46:31.103
Well. it's official. I'm
never sleeping again. ever.

370
00:46:31.896 --> 00:46:33.146
You okay?

371
00:46:34.107 --> 00:46:36.358
A guy cuts words
into his chest.

372
00:46:36.442 --> 00:46:38.235
Someone else nails him
to the ceiling.

373
00:46:38.861 --> 00:46:40.445
What's not okay?

374
00:46:42.031 --> 00:46:43.573
So where we going?

375
00:46:43.783 --> 00:46:46.910
The girl. I got to talk to
her. find out what she knows.

376
00:46:46.953 --> 00:46:49.287
Wait. wait. we don't have a name. all right?
That would help.

377
00:46:49.372 --> 00:46:53.458
Well. maybe we do. Maybe it's
not "Christ in New York."

378
00:46:53.793 --> 00:46:57.212
Maybe it's "Chris in New York."
"Christine in New York."

379
00:46:57.588 --> 00:46:59.297
"Christine York."

380
00:46:59.382 --> 00:47:02.843
Let's run a DMV check and find out
if any of those names come up.

381
00:47:08.975 --> 00:47:12.352
Hello. Christine York. Sometimes
you border on competent.

382
00:47:13.312 --> 00:47:14.980
I know. It's scary. isn't it?

383
00:47:23.823 --> 00:47:25.198
Christine?

384
00:47:25.742 --> 00:47:28.910
Mabel called. She'd like you to get
dressed and join her for lunch.

385
00:47:28.995 --> 00:47:30.412
Grazie. Carson.

386
00:48:05.448 --> 00:48:06.698
No!

387
00:48:23.841 --> 00:48:24.883
Shit!

388
00:49:04.674 --> 00:49:07.217
No! No!

389
00:49:09.136 --> 00:49:10.220
Help!

390
00:49:10.263 --> 00:49:11.596
Goddamn it. get off of me!

391
00:49:11.681 --> 00:49:13.682
Go downstairs and watch
the front door! Please!

392
00:49:13.766 --> 00:49:16.518
Help! There is no
sanctuary but heaven.

393
00:49:17.728 --> 00:49:19.271
You must go there now.
What are you doing?

394
00:49:19.355 --> 00:49:21.523
I commend you to Almighty
God and entrust you...

395
00:49:22.108 --> 00:49:26.486
At what point is this considered
interfering with a police investigation?

396
00:49:26.696 --> 00:49:30.740
Hey. we are private citizens having a
conversation with another citizen.

397
00:49:30.825 --> 00:49:33.660
I mean. I don't think they've
found a way to outlaw that.

398
00:49:33.744 --> 00:49:35.203
At least not yet.

399
00:49:36.956 --> 00:49:39.124
Please! No!

400
00:49:41.669 --> 00:49:42.794
May you return to him...

401
00:49:53.097 --> 00:49:54.598
Go down there.
Do whatever you can.

402
00:49:54.640 --> 00:49:56.516
I need more time
to finish the last rites.

403
00:49:56.601 --> 00:49:59.060
- May Christ. the true shepherd...
- Help!

404
00:49:59.562 --> 00:50:00.979
- Stairs.
- Covered.

405
00:50:05.484 --> 00:50:06.776
Help!

406
00:50:12.241 --> 00:50:13.783
May you see your redeemer...

407
00:50:19.999 --> 00:50:21.416
Forever. Amen.

408
00:51:02.792 --> 00:51:04.084
Son of a bitch!

409
00:51:27.858 --> 00:51:29.275
You all right?

410
00:51:30.111 --> 00:51:32.904
Yeah. Check the body
down the stairs.

411
00:51:33.739 --> 00:51:35.198
What body?

412
00:51:37.827 --> 00:51:40.286
Call the police
and get an ambulance.

413
00:51:43.457 --> 00:51:48.169
Take it easy. We're the good guys.
All right? What happened?

414
00:51:50.131 --> 00:51:52.007
Carson. Those men...

415
00:51:53.134 --> 00:51:55.510
Those men.
they tried to kill me.

416
00:51:56.429 --> 00:51:57.595
Why?

417
00:51:59.473 --> 00:52:02.600
Eight jets. variable speed. That's
what I call dying in style.

418
00:52:02.685 --> 00:52:04.644
What kind of girl lives
in a house like this anyway?

419
00:52:04.729 --> 00:52:07.063
Oh. she's an orphan.
Both parents deceased.

420
00:52:07.106 --> 00:52:10.191
After her mother died. the
home nurse married the father.

421
00:52:10.276 --> 00:52:12.318
Now the nurse
is the sole guardian.

422
00:52:12.403 --> 00:52:14.779
I think it's adorable the way
you talk like a real cop.

423
00:52:14.822 --> 00:52:17.657
Yeah? So you think maybe after they
clean up this mess. we could...

424
00:52:17.742 --> 00:52:19.701
- Don't tempt me.
- soak a little?

425
00:52:49.315 --> 00:52:50.690
They relax me. You want one?

426
00:52:50.775 --> 00:52:52.984
Oh. no. thanks. I drink.

427
00:52:54.236 --> 00:52:56.279
My little girl
had one just like it.

428
00:52:56.322 --> 00:52:57.530
Really?

429
00:52:57.615 --> 00:53:00.784
Yeah? You snoop through her
stuff without asking. too?

430
00:53:01.952 --> 00:53:03.995
When I was looking
for something.

431
00:53:04.038 --> 00:53:05.914
What are you looking for?

432
00:53:06.665 --> 00:53:08.541
A connection.

433
00:53:08.626 --> 00:53:11.002
Most days. I don't feel
connected to anyone.

434
00:53:11.879 --> 00:53:14.798
I noticed a lot of
religious books outside.

435
00:53:16.383 --> 00:53:17.592
They're my stepmother's.

436
00:53:17.676 --> 00:53:19.052
Is she a big believer?

437
00:53:19.136 --> 00:53:20.261
No. not really.

438
00:53:20.346 --> 00:53:22.847
It's mostly just kind of
like a hobby with her.

439
00:53:22.932 --> 00:53:26.184
Do you know a priest by the
name of Thomas Aquinas?

440
00:53:26.268 --> 00:53:29.354
No. Is that your connection?
Religion?

441
00:53:29.396 --> 00:53:31.189
I've seen a lot of
attempted murders.

442
00:53:31.232 --> 00:53:33.691
but I've never seen anyone
perform the last rites before.

443
00:53:33.734 --> 00:53:35.443
- Christine?
- In here!

444
00:53:37.363 --> 00:53:40.615
Are you all right? Oh. my God.
I just heard what happened.

445
00:53:42.034 --> 00:53:43.159
Did they hurt you?

446
00:53:43.202 --> 00:53:45.245
I'm okay. but Carson...

447
00:53:45.329 --> 00:53:46.913
I know.

448
00:53:49.250 --> 00:53:52.085
I'm just so glad
you came along when you did.

449
00:53:52.711 --> 00:53:53.962
Thanks.

450
00:54:19.613 --> 00:54:23.575
I didn't realize you knew where the
library was. let alone had a card.

451
00:54:24.994 --> 00:54:27.162
Well. there's
a lot about me you don't know.

452
00:54:31.625 --> 00:54:32.959
They're right outside.

453
00:54:33.043 --> 00:54:35.628
- You must bring her here.
- He is waiting for her.

454
00:54:35.713 --> 00:54:38.798
No. that's impossible! They'll
follow me and find the temple!

455
00:54:42.219 --> 00:54:44.137
I couldn't convince her
to come here.

456
00:54:49.727 --> 00:54:50.768
Yuck!

457
00:54:50.811 --> 00:54:53.354
Then I shall have to go to her.

458
00:54:54.023 --> 00:54:55.607
Did I mention
I had a date tonight?

459
00:54:55.691 --> 00:54:58.193
Not just the inflatable kind.
A real live girl.

460
00:54:58.277 --> 00:55:00.528
Did you break up
with the inflatable one?

461
00:55:00.613 --> 00:55:01.905
Yeah.

462
00:55:03.115 --> 00:55:05.909
She was just too needy.
Everything was about her.

463
00:55:06.619 --> 00:55:09.287
It's just that with this. it's
starting to feel a lot like work.

464
00:55:09.580 --> 00:55:13.333
Normally. I wouldn't mind work.
because. well. you know.

465
00:55:13.667 --> 00:55:15.460
we'd be getting paid.

466
00:55:15.544 --> 00:55:18.588
Watching rich people for free.
It just seems odd. doesn't it?

467
00:55:22.218 --> 00:55:23.885
Okay. I'll wait here.

468
00:55:32.811 --> 00:55:34.312
Change your mind
about the pill?

469
00:55:34.396 --> 00:55:35.438
I found something.

470
00:55:39.068 --> 00:55:41.486
Christine. what are you doing?
Why is that man here?

471
00:55:41.654 --> 00:55:43.446
I'll be five minutes.

472
00:55:43.989 --> 00:55:46.824
She loves me to death. but
she's a little overprotective.

473
00:56:11.433 --> 00:56:13.685
I took this from
one of your attackers.

474
00:56:13.769 --> 00:56:16.312
- Did you show that to the police?
- No.

475
00:56:16.438 --> 00:56:19.190
If I did. it would just end up
in a small plastic envelope

476
00:56:19.233 --> 00:56:20.692
on one of their large shelves.

477
00:56:20.734 --> 00:56:21.901
That's pretty cynical.

478
00:56:21.986 --> 00:56:26.614
Well. I've put a few of those envelopes
up on that large shelf myself.

479
00:56:26.907 --> 00:56:28.449
I used to be a cop.

480
00:56:29.660 --> 00:56:32.120
Now. this amulet
is from a Masonic order

481
00:56:32.204 --> 00:56:35.832
in a former sub-herald
of the Vatican Knights.

482
00:56:35.874 --> 00:56:37.500
The Knights of the Holy See.

483
00:56:37.543 --> 00:56:40.712
They await the return
of the Dark Angel to earth.

484
00:56:41.171 --> 00:56:44.716
So. the men that attacked me
are devil worshipers?

485
00:56:44.758 --> 00:56:48.261
No. This says they're
the good guys.

486
00:56:48.345 --> 00:56:51.055
They're the ones that are supposed
to stop the devil worshipers.

487
00:56:51.098 --> 00:56:54.267
- Those were the good guys?
- What does that have to do with me?

488
00:57:05.070 --> 00:57:07.905
I'm sorry.
I have a medical condition.

489
00:57:07.948 --> 00:57:09.949
Sometimes I see things
that aren't there.

490
00:57:10.034 --> 00:57:13.578
No. I saw it. too.

491
00:57:41.023 --> 00:57:43.024
I've been having visions
ever since I can remember.

492
00:57:43.108 --> 00:57:45.026
but I've never
shared one before.

493
00:57:45.652 --> 00:57:47.612
There must be an explanation.

494
00:57:47.654 --> 00:57:50.073
I hope so because I've been
waiting all my life to hear it.

495
00:58:50.717 --> 00:58:52.301
Let's get out of here! Come on!

496
00:58:53.679 --> 00:58:55.138
You're not going anywhere.

497
00:58:55.180 --> 00:58:57.390
- What are you doing?
- There's no time to discuss this.

498
00:58:59.935 --> 00:59:02.311
After all these years of
waiting. it's finally happening.

499
00:59:02.354 --> 00:59:03.479
What's happening?

500
00:59:03.522 --> 00:59:04.981
You can't run away now!

501
00:59:07.359 --> 00:59:09.277
Stop it! Let her go!

502
00:59:09.361 --> 00:59:10.361
No!

503
00:59:14.533 --> 00:59:16.200
Right now!

504
00:59:18.162 --> 00:59:19.412
Shit!

505
00:59:20.289 --> 00:59:21.998
Don't you love me?

506
00:59:22.875 --> 00:59:25.042
Didn't I give you everything?

507
00:59:25.836 --> 00:59:28.212
Haven't I been a mother to you?

508
00:59:48.400 --> 00:59:50.067
No!

509
00:59:50.110 --> 00:59:51.235
Oh. my God!

510
01:00:05.334 --> 01:00:07.502
- Christine.
- Oh. no.

511
01:00:07.586 --> 01:00:09.754
You know who I am.
I've come for you.

512
01:00:09.796 --> 01:00:11.506
Let's go. Come on.

513
01:00:28.398 --> 01:00:32.527
You only had one simple job
and you couldn't even do that.

514
01:00:47.960 --> 01:00:51.295
Hey. Marge? Marge. over here!
We need your help!

515
01:00:51.922 --> 01:00:53.130
Easy with the hardware.

516
01:00:56.426 --> 01:00:58.261
Jesus. Marge! What the fuck?

517
01:00:59.972 --> 01:01:02.640
It's okay. Jer.
We just want the girl.

518
01:01:03.183 --> 01:01:04.934
Okay. tell me what the
hell is going on here?

519
01:01:04.977 --> 01:01:07.645
- I don't know.
- I don't believe you.

520
01:01:08.522 --> 01:01:11.315
- All right. I'm coming out.
- Throw out the gun.

521
01:01:11.358 --> 01:01:14.068
Please don't leave me here.
Please!

522
01:01:21.410 --> 01:01:22.827
Hands on your head.

523
01:01:23.036 --> 01:01:26.330
- What?
- Hands on your head. Now!

524
01:01:34.506 --> 01:01:36.382
What do you want with her. Marge?

525
01:01:36.675 --> 01:01:38.634
Why is she so important?

526
01:01:38.677 --> 01:01:40.678
Just the girl.
You can kill him.

527
01:01:55.652 --> 01:01:57.320
Come on! Quickly.

528
01:02:15.922 --> 01:02:17.715
You. I don't need.

529
01:02:17.924 --> 01:02:19.216
But you...

530
01:02:21.219 --> 01:02:23.971
Call your people. Find them.

531
01:02:40.989 --> 01:02:42.323
Over here.

532
01:02:47.245 --> 01:02:48.537
Goddamn it!

533
01:02:49.748 --> 01:02:53.084
Get up. Come on. Get up!

534
01:02:53.168 --> 01:02:54.919
My best friend is dead.

535
01:02:54.961 --> 01:02:57.838
Everyone is trying to kill us.
I just shot two cops.

536
01:02:57.923 --> 01:02:59.090
Why is everyone after you?

537
01:02:59.174 --> 01:03:01.258
I don't know.
I swear. I don't know.

538
01:03:01.343 --> 01:03:02.843
Why is this happening?

539
01:03:03.095 --> 01:03:06.097
I know it's my fault.
I just don't know why.

540
01:03:07.766 --> 01:03:11.060
That man on the stairs.
what do you know about him?

541
01:03:11.186 --> 01:03:13.854
- Nothing.
- Come on.I saw your face.

542
01:03:13.939 --> 01:03:16.774
- You recognized him.
- I don't talk about it.

543
01:03:16.942 --> 01:03:19.360
Tell me. I need to know.

544
01:03:23.657 --> 01:03:25.157
I've seen him before.

545
01:03:26.993 --> 01:03:28.285
In my dreams.

546
01:03:29.413 --> 01:03:32.164
- In your dreams?
- They're nightmares. really.

547
01:03:32.249 --> 01:03:37.044
He takes me
and he makes love to me.

548
01:03:37.629 --> 01:03:39.338
I've been making love to him
my whole life.

549
01:03:39.423 --> 01:03:43.175
I thought I was crazy. but he
was never real before tonight.

550
01:03:43.260 --> 01:03:45.803
Oh. he's real.
I've seen him before.

551
01:03:46.638 --> 01:03:47.805
I'm afraid.

552
01:03:48.098 --> 01:03:50.933
Don't be afraid. I won't let
him do any harm to you.

553
01:03:50.976 --> 01:03:55.396
I'm afraid of me. I'm afraid that if
I see him. if he tries to take me.

554
01:03:55.480 --> 01:03:57.440
I'm gonna want him to.

555
01:04:00.652 --> 01:04:01.861
Let's go!

556
01:04:02.279 --> 01:04:04.405
- Where are we going?
- To get some answers.

557
01:04:16.209 --> 01:04:18.252
You don't need that.
You have no enemies here.

558
01:04:18.336 --> 01:04:22.006
I'm not so sure about that. This girl
was just attacked by your people.

559
01:04:22.090 --> 01:04:25.801
- Your Vatican Knights almost killed her!
- Vatican Knights?

560
01:04:26.428 --> 01:04:27.636
Oh. my God.

561
01:04:28.597 --> 01:04:31.599
Well. they're not my people. They think
they're doing God's work. but they're not.

562
01:04:31.683 --> 01:04:34.435
I want to know what's going on
and I want to know right now.

563
01:04:34.519 --> 01:04:37.271
All right. put the gun away.
Did anybody see you come?

564
01:04:39.065 --> 01:04:42.276
- No.
- Good. We should be safe here.

565
01:04:42.861 --> 01:04:46.989
According to the scriptures. he can't
see inside of the house of God.

566
01:04:47.949 --> 01:04:50.701
- Who can't?
- Maybe now you're ready to believe.

567
01:05:09.346 --> 01:05:10.429
Her hands are healed.

568
01:05:10.514 --> 01:05:12.223
That's the power of faith.

569
01:05:12.265 --> 01:05:14.600
- Who is she?
- She's a Polish peasant.

570
01:05:14.684 --> 01:05:16.644
She fell into a trance
about two weeks ago.

571
01:05:16.728 --> 01:05:19.897
and then she began to speak in a language
she couldn't possibly have known.

572
01:05:19.981 --> 01:05:22.608
And she made a prophecy
about End of Days.

573
01:05:22.692 --> 01:05:23.734
End of Days?

574
01:05:23.777 --> 01:05:27.238
Of man's destruction and the
Unholy's reign upon the earth.

575
01:05:27.447 --> 01:05:31.116
Why don't you stop all this church talk
and tell us what the hell is going on?

576
01:05:31.201 --> 01:05:32.201
Who's after her?

577
01:05:32.244 --> 01:05:34.995
Well. if you'll excuse me.
I'll try to explain.

578
01:05:36.248 --> 01:05:38.791
Do you know anything
about the Number of the Beast?

579
01:05:38.875 --> 01:05:41.669
Revelation of St. John?
From his dream?

580
01:05:41.962 --> 01:05:42.962
666?

581
01:05:43.046 --> 01:05:45.756
The Number of the Beast
is not 666.

582
01:05:45.799 --> 01:05:50.010
Often in dreams. numbers appear
upside down and backwards.

583
01:05:50.095 --> 01:05:53.931
So. 666 becomes 999.

584
01:05:54.015 --> 01:05:57.434
Like in 1999.
the year of his return.

585
01:05:57.477 --> 01:05:59.353
What does that
have to do with me?

586
01:06:02.983 --> 01:06:04.942
The return of Satan.

587
01:06:05.026 --> 01:06:07.653
Does any of this
look familiar to you?

588
01:06:18.957 --> 01:06:22.293
She's been chosen.
He's in her blood.

589
01:06:23.169 --> 01:06:27.131
The Holy Church has been searching
for you since the day you were born.

590
01:06:27.173 --> 01:06:30.217
- Chosen for what?
- Every thousand years. on the eve of the millennium.

591
01:06:30.302 --> 01:06:32.219
the Dark Angel comes
and takes a body

592
01:06:32.304 --> 01:06:36.473
and then he walks the earth. looking
for a woman who will bear his child.

593
01:06:36.558 --> 01:06:41.312
It all has to happen in that unholy
hour before midnight on New Year's Eve.

594
01:06:41.646 --> 01:06:44.815
If he consummates your flesh
with his human body.

595
01:06:44.858 --> 01:06:47.651
then he unlocks
the gate of hell

596
01:06:47.736 --> 01:06:51.655
and everything as we know it
ceases to exist.

597
01:06:51.740 --> 01:06:54.783
So. the Prince of Darkness
wants to conquer the earth.

598
01:06:54.826 --> 01:06:57.995
but he has to wait until an hour
before midnight of New Year's Eve?

599
01:06:58.038 --> 01:06:59.121
Is this Eastern time?

600
01:06:59.164 --> 01:07:01.081
It's got nothing to do
with New Year's Eve.

601
01:07:01.166 --> 01:07:03.792
It has to do with a temporary
celestial alignment.

602
01:07:03.835 --> 01:07:06.337
The Gregorian monks
studied the heavens.

603
01:07:06.379 --> 01:07:10.215
They were able to calculate the
precise moment of this event.

604
01:07:10.300 --> 01:07:12.968
They created our calendar
by mapping this event

605
01:07:13.011 --> 01:07:15.554
and counting backwards
from that moment.

606
01:07:15.639 --> 01:07:17.514
I think it was a mistake
to come here.

607
01:07:17.599 --> 01:07:19.224
It doesn't matter whether
you believe or not.

608
01:07:19.309 --> 01:07:22.519
He's real and he won't rest
till he finds this girl.

609
01:07:22.812 --> 01:07:23.896
Why did he pick me?

610
01:07:23.980 --> 01:07:26.690
Because the stars were right
when you were born.

611
01:07:26.733 --> 01:07:29.860
A man's body was also chosen.
just like yours.

612
01:07:29.945 --> 01:07:33.864
If the devil does exist. why
doesn't your God do anything?

613
01:07:33.949 --> 01:07:35.199
It's not my God.

614
01:07:35.283 --> 01:07:38.911
It's our God. and he doesn't
say that he will save us.

615
01:07:38.995 --> 01:07:42.164
He says that we will
save ourselves.

616
01:07:42.332 --> 01:07:45.584
Save myself? What am I supposed to do?
Get a restraining order?

617
01:07:46.127 --> 01:07:48.712
- We have to have faith.
- Faith.

618
01:07:48.755 --> 01:07:50.798
Yes. faith.
It's an interesting concept.

619
01:07:50.882 --> 01:07:54.176
If you read the Bible.
you can't miss it. Faith!

620
01:07:54.886 --> 01:07:57.721
Between your faith
and my Glock 9 mm.

621
01:07:57.806 --> 01:08:00.391
I take my Glock.
Come. let's go.

622
01:08:00.433 --> 01:08:04.019
I'm afraid it takes a person of
pure heart to defeat pure evil.

623
01:08:04.062 --> 01:08:06.397
You did your job. You brought
her here to people of faith.

624
01:08:06.481 --> 01:08:08.232
We'll protect her.
We'll hide her.

625
01:08:08.316 --> 01:08:11.026
You know. you live
in a different world.

626
01:08:11.611 --> 01:08:15.739
We have some real serious problems
here and this is not solving them.

627
01:08:15.824 --> 01:08:19.034
Satan's greatest trick was
convincing man he didn't exist.

628
01:08:22.580 --> 01:08:26.208
I don't...
This all feels true to me.

629
01:08:28.169 --> 01:08:29.461
You'll be safer with me.

630
01:08:29.546 --> 01:08:32.297
At least. I can fight this guy
with something real.

631
01:08:33.091 --> 01:08:35.592
You know what to do.
You feel it.

632
01:08:45.937 --> 01:08:47.312
I'm sorry.

633
01:08:50.567 --> 01:08:51.775
Let him go.

634
01:09:20.847 --> 01:09:23.474
It gets easier when
you accept what you are.

635
01:09:23.516 --> 01:09:25.142
A fallen soul.

636
01:09:30.857 --> 01:09:33.150
Door's locked.
no windows broken.

637
01:09:33.234 --> 01:09:36.695
- How did I get in here?
- Who the fuck are you?

638
01:09:36.780 --> 01:09:39.198
Oh. I think you know who I am.

639
01:09:39.532 --> 01:09:41.325
You just don't want to
believe it.

640
01:09:43.745 --> 01:09:46.747
I took a bullet for you.
I protected you.

641
01:09:46.831 --> 01:09:49.666
Oh. no. no. you didn't protect me.
You protected this body.

642
01:09:49.709 --> 01:09:51.835
Am I getting a pattern here?

643
01:09:52.879 --> 01:09:56.840
So much pain. "Not to be
taken with alcohol."

644
01:09:58.009 --> 01:09:59.426
Remember that.

645
01:10:02.847 --> 01:10:05.224
To lose a wife and child.

646
01:10:07.060 --> 01:10:10.354
I can't even imagine
what that must be like.

647
01:10:10.772 --> 01:10:14.191
- What do you want?
- To make you happy again.

648
01:10:35.004 --> 01:10:36.755
A gift from your daughter?

649
01:10:47.225 --> 01:10:48.267
Amy?

650
01:10:48.351 --> 01:10:51.061
Don't stay in there too long.
You'll turn into a prune.

651
01:10:51.104 --> 01:10:52.146
Emily.

652
01:10:52.230 --> 01:10:53.897
Come on. darling.
It's time to get out.

653
01:10:55.233 --> 01:10:57.734
Got to get you dressed. Your
daddy's gonna be home soon.

654
01:10:57.777 --> 01:10:59.820
I have the best daddy
in the whole world.

655
01:10:59.904 --> 01:11:01.947
Yes. you certainly do.

656
01:11:02.824 --> 01:11:04.741
But I don't think
he'll be home.

657
01:11:04.784 --> 01:11:07.119
Now. what makes you say
a silly thing like that?

658
01:11:07.203 --> 01:11:08.579
He never comes home.

659
01:11:08.621 --> 01:11:10.539
Well. honey. you know
your daddy works hard.

660
01:11:10.582 --> 01:11:13.750
It's not about how much time you're there.
It's about "quality time."

661
01:11:13.918 --> 01:11:17.212
Now. he'll be home just like he promised.
You'll see.

662
01:11:17.255 --> 01:11:19.214
He keeps his promises.

663
01:11:20.008 --> 01:11:23.427
I can give it all back to you.
Everything that he took away.

664
01:11:23.803 --> 01:11:24.970
Everything.

665
01:11:26.139 --> 01:11:28.265
You can hold your wife again.

666
01:11:28.725 --> 01:11:31.935
You can watch your daughter walk
through the door in her prom dress.

667
01:11:32.270 --> 01:11:35.147
All you have to do
is tell me where the girl is.

668
01:11:35.231 --> 01:11:38.358
Come on. She's a nobody to you.
You don't even know her.

669
01:11:38.776 --> 01:11:41.528
You're in the middle of something
you don't really understand.

670
01:11:41.613 --> 01:11:44.948
You think you're saving her from me?
She wants to be with me.

671
01:11:44.991 --> 01:11:46.283
You know that.

672
01:11:46.367 --> 01:11:48.035
So. what did you do
in school today?

673
01:11:48.119 --> 01:11:51.580
You think I'd harm her?
I'd treat her like a queen.

674
01:11:52.165 --> 01:11:55.250
You told me once you'd do
anything to get your family back.

675
01:11:56.044 --> 01:11:58.962
You want them?
This is your chance.

676
01:11:59.464 --> 01:12:01.757
They're not real.
Does that matter?

677
01:12:02.217 --> 01:12:03.467
Oh. yes.

678
01:12:03.843 --> 01:12:07.262
I think you need to be reminded
of how painful reality is.

679
01:12:09.349 --> 01:12:10.599
No!

680
01:12:31.454 --> 01:12:33.163
Don't hurt my baby!

681
01:12:33.206 --> 01:12:34.373
Daddy!

682
01:12:34.457 --> 01:12:36.166
Let my daughter go!

683
01:12:38.586 --> 01:12:40.003
Daddy!

684
01:12:40.672 --> 01:12:42.381
Let go of my baby!

685
01:12:48.179 --> 01:12:49.346
No!

686
01:12:53.101 --> 01:12:54.601
Oh. it's true.

687
01:12:55.228 --> 01:12:56.228
Oh. no.

688
01:13:12.912 --> 01:13:14.871
It wasn't your fault.

689
01:13:15.081 --> 01:13:17.416
- I wasn't there.
- No. you were just...

690
01:13:17.500 --> 01:13:19.167
You were out doing your job.

691
01:13:19.210 --> 01:13:21.336
I wasn't fucking there!

692
01:13:21.379 --> 01:13:24.381
Oh. look at you.
Torn apart by guilt.

693
01:13:24.549 --> 01:13:25.757
You didn't do anything wrong.

694
01:13:25.842 --> 01:13:28.385
You were an honest cop.
You didn't take money.

695
01:13:28.428 --> 01:13:32.014
You had to testify against them even
after they threatened your family.

696
01:13:32.056 --> 01:13:34.099
Most people would never
testify against those guys.

697
01:13:34.183 --> 01:13:36.601
They're not like you.
You had to do the right thing.

698
01:13:36.686 --> 01:13:40.063
And where was God? He could've
stopped it. but he didn't.

699
01:13:40.148 --> 01:13:42.107
He fucked you. And then
he made you feel guilty.

700
01:13:42.191 --> 01:13:45.235
Me. I don't do guilt. I
didn't do what happened here.

701
01:13:45.278 --> 01:13:48.363
He did.
Now you just think about that.

702
01:13:48.406 --> 01:13:50.240
Then you tell me
who's really your friend.

703
01:13:51.034 --> 01:13:53.285
I can make it like
it never happened.

704
01:13:53.369 --> 01:13:55.871
All for the price of
a stranger's address.

705
01:13:57.457 --> 01:13:58.540
No!

706
01:14:00.960 --> 01:14:02.878
You will never see the girl!

707
01:14:02.920 --> 01:14:05.881
Now. you see.
Now you're upsetting me.

708
01:14:06.424 --> 01:14:09.009
You don't want to
see me upset. believe me.

709
01:14:09.093 --> 01:14:12.804
Oh. you want to fuck with me?
You think you know bad?

710
01:14:12.889 --> 01:14:16.850
You're a fucking choirboy
compared to me! A choirboy!

711
01:14:17.101 --> 01:14:19.603
You're in touch with your anger.
I really like that.

712
01:14:20.313 --> 01:14:22.856
I don't know about you.
but I'm gonna have a drink.

713
01:14:22.940 --> 01:14:25.817
You and I are so much alike.

714
01:14:25.902 --> 01:14:28.403
We're nothing alike! Nothing!

715
01:14:28.446 --> 01:14:32.074
Look at yourself. Look at this.
Look at what you are now.

716
01:14:32.116 --> 01:14:35.452
You walked away from the light just like me.
You want one?

717
01:14:35.912 --> 01:14:37.371
You need to get out. now.

718
01:14:37.455 --> 01:14:39.915
Come on.
You know what's in your heart.

719
01:14:39.957 --> 01:14:41.208
We're on the same side.

720
01:14:41.292 --> 01:14:43.960
I'm not on your side.
and I never will be.

721
01:14:44.003 --> 01:14:47.589
What. you're on his side? He's the
one who took away your family.

722
01:14:47.965 --> 01:14:50.050
Let me tell you something
about him.

723
01:14:50.426 --> 01:14:53.220
He is the biggest
underachiever of all time.

724
01:14:53.304 --> 01:14:55.639
He just had
a good publicist. that's all.

725
01:14:55.723 --> 01:14:57.682
Something good happens.
"It's his will."

726
01:14:57.767 --> 01:15:01.103
Something bad happens.
"He moves in mysterious ways."

727
01:15:01.145 --> 01:15:04.356
You take that overblown press
kit they call the Bible.

728
01:15:04.440 --> 01:15:06.650
You look for the answer in
there. what do they tell you?

729
01:15:06.692 --> 01:15:09.194
"Shit happens." Please.

730
01:15:10.029 --> 01:15:13.156
He treated you like garbage.
You walked away.

731
01:15:14.075 --> 01:15:15.826
I'm not the bad guy.

732
01:15:17.662 --> 01:15:20.080
What about the End of Days?

733
01:15:20.164 --> 01:15:23.333
Think of it as a new beginning.
A change of management.

734
01:15:23.418 --> 01:15:25.710
And you'll be right there
with me on the ground floor.

735
01:15:25.795 --> 01:15:28.130
It will be so cool.

736
01:15:29.006 --> 01:15:30.841
Tell me what you want.

737
01:15:30.925 --> 01:15:34.344
Tell me what you really want
and I'll give it to you.

738
01:15:37.932 --> 01:15:40.016
I'll tell you what I want.

739
01:15:42.728 --> 01:15:46.440
I want you to go to hell.

740
01:15:48.359 --> 01:15:50.861
You see.
sometimes the problem is

741
01:15:52.363 --> 01:15:56.783
hell comes to you!

742
01:16:10.590 --> 01:16:13.216
Don't fuck up the coat.

743
01:16:16.345 --> 01:16:17.971
I've wasted too much time
on this.

